statement.p:
If we wanted to, we could have written the formula for P as a function of t by composing the two functions:
                    C \amp= f(t) = 5e^{-0.058t}
                    P \amp= g(C) = -12.5C + 172.5

li.p:
The formula for f(g(x)) is:
                    f(g(x)) \amp= f\left(x^2\right)
                    \amp= \frac{x^2}{x^2+4}

