solution.p:
Solving for t:
              500\left(1.03\right)^t \amp= 925
              1.03^t \amp= \frac{925}{500}
              \ln\left(1.03^t\right) \amp= \ln\left(\frac{925}{500}\right)
              t\cdot \ln\left(1.03\right) \amp= \ln\left(\frac{925}{500}\right)
              t \amp= \frac{\ln\left(\frac{925}{500}\right)}{\ln\left(1.03\right)}
              \amp\approx 20.81 \text{ years}

The input for the inverse function is dollars, so we just evaluate:
              B^{-1}(1200) \amp= \frac{\ln\left(\frac{1200}{500}\right)}{\ln (1.03)}
              \amp\approx 29.62 \text{ years}

